President Donald Trump has announced a plan to improve and invest in America's infrastructure. The proposal aims to change how infrastructure is built, financed, and maintained across the country. The plan includes stimulating at least $1.5 trillion in infrastructure investment, with $200 billion in direct federal funding. The focus is not only on roads and bridges, but also on drinking and wastewater, energy, broadband, and veterans hospitals. The proposal aims to provide federal dollars as matching funds to incentivize infrastructure investment, address the needs of rural communities, streamline project delivery, and provide workforce training. The plan empowers state and local officials to make decisions regarding infrastructure needs in their communities. The op-ed emphasizes that infrastructure is crucial for the economy, job growth, and maintaining competitiveness.